org.eclipse.papyrus.designer.languages.java.reverse.javaparser.ast

Class ImportDeclaration

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.eclipse.papyrus.designer.languages.java.reverse.javaparser.ast.Node
      • org.eclipse.papyrus.designer.languages.java.reverse.javaparser.ast.ImportDeclaration
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    Cloneable

    public final class ImportDeclaration
extends Node

    This class represents a import declaration or an empty import declaration. Imports are optional for the CompilationUnit.

    The ImportDeclaration is constructed following the syntax:
     
 ImportDeclaration ::= "import" ( "static" )? NameExpr ( "." "*" )? ";"
    An enmpty import declaration is simply a semicolon among the import declarations.
    Author:
    Julio Vilmar Gesser
